High School- https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/CTKSXWD

‚ÄúWhen parents call to say their child missed the bus and they can't bring them to school because they're already at work, I offer to go pick the student up. When a student is having a rough day, I try to make them feel better by being funny or offering them a snack. Sometimes I even offer to tutor students who need extra help, even though I'm no longer a tutor. I am 100% here for our students and families and will always be.‚Äù
-Great Oaks Staff Member

We are not just staff‚Äìwe are mentors, we are a support team, we are a community.

post_text: For the best remote learning experience, it's important to follow a learning routine. Each day will be a bit different, but try waking up and going to bed at the same time each weekday. It's also helpful to separate your work area from your relaxation area, so try to avoid working from your bed (even though it's tempting)!
text: For the best remote learning experience, it's important to follow a learning routine. Each day will be a bit different, but try waking up and going to bed at the same time each weekday. It's also helpful to separate your work area from your relaxation area, so try to avoid working from your bed (even though it's tempting)!

Great Oaks Legacy Charter School
January 20, 2015 at 1:14 PM ¬∑

Great Oaks Charter School in Newark's middle school students participated in a Math Symposium last week, where among the activities were logic problems, brain teasers, and a Barbie bungee jump (rubber band forecasting) challenge. Students had a great time learning real applications for math. Check out the photos here.

Great Oaks Legacy Charter School
November 21, 2014 at 4:25 PM ¬∑

Yesterday, Great Oaks Charter School in Newark held its Digital Learning Night and Parent Potluck. It was also the last evening of our food drive to benefit the Community Food Bank of NJ. We contributed over 1,000 lbs of food to families in need! See photos of our students, parents, and staff in action!
